Real part: (2 + √2) - 2 = √2
Imaginary part: (-3 - 3√2) - (-3) = (-3 - 3√2) + 3 = -3√2

So, z - c = √2 - 3√2 i

Now, we need to rotate this translated point by π/4 radians counter-clockwise. The rotation can be achieved by multiplying by e^(iπ/4). 

