So, that seems correct. So, the first peak is at \( x = -\frac{\pi}{6} \), which is \( \frac{\pi}{6} \) units to the left of the origin. But the phase shift is \( -\frac{\pi}{3} \), which is \( \frac{\pi}{3} \) units to the left.

