To find the result when the greatest common factor (GCF) of 6432 and 132 is increased by 11, we start by determining the GCF using the Euclidean algorithm.

1. Divide 6432 by 132: 
   \[
   6432 \div 132 = 48 \text{ remainder } 96
   \]
