So, the problem involves two regular polygons: a hexagon and an octagon. Both are regular, meaning all their sides are equal, and all their angles are equal too. The hexagon has a side length of 16 cm, and the octagon has the same perimeter as this hexagon. My task is to find the side length of the octagon.

