To find the length of each side of the regular octagon, we start by calculating the perimeter of the given regular hexagon. The hexagon has a side length of 16 cm, so its perimeter is:

\[
\text{Perimeter of hexagon} = 6 \times 16 \, \text{cm} = 96 \, \text{cm}
\]

Since the regular octagon has the same perimeter as the hexagon, the perimeter of the octagon is also 96 cm. A regular octagon has 8 equal sides, so we divide the perimeter by 8 to find the length of each side:

\[
\text{Side length of octagon} = \frac{96 \, \text{cm}}{8} = 12 \, \text{cm}
\]

Thus, the length of each side of the octagon is \boxed{12} cm.
